1
00:00:02,750 --> 00:00:04,458
What did you say to Phil?

2
00:00:04,458 --> 00:00:05,833
Why'd he bail
all of a sudden?

3
00:00:06,958 --> 00:00:07,958
Hey,

4
00:00:08,416 --> 00:00:10,125
can I at least
finish breakfast?

5
00:00:10,125 --> 00:00:12,875
Lisa's getting in early today.

6
00:00:14,250 --> 00:00:18,166
Oh, crap! Lisa's here!
I'm so dead!

7
00:00:18,166 --> 00:00:19,000
Morning, Lisa.

8
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,541
Your coffee,
75 degrees as usual?

9
00:00:23,375 --> 00:00:25,041
Is this your first day?

10
00:00:26,625 --> 00:00:28,000
Okay! On it.

11
00:00:44,291 --> 00:00:46,583
These are the cast bios
for the show.

12
00:00:50,125 --> 00:00:51,666
This is the title.

13
00:00:51,666 --> 00:00:54,083
Then the profile
starts below.

14
00:00:58,708 --> 00:01:00,125
Why the paper airplane?

15
00:01:00,125 --> 00:01:02,000
Is there a story
behind it?

16
00:01:03,125 --> 00:01:04,833
It looks great.

17
00:01:10,291 --> 00:01:12,333
This cover
tells me nothing.

18
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:14,000
Neither do these
pointless effects.

19
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,958
You just wasted
10 seconds.

20
00:01:15,958 --> 00:01:18,583
I review at least
40 decks a day.

21
00:01:18,583 --> 00:01:19,916
If every deck

22
00:01:19,916 --> 00:01:22,083
has five things like this,

23
00:01:22,875 --> 00:01:24,666
that's over

24
00:01:25,291 --> 00:01:27,000
33 minutes a day.

25
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:29,583
I could write

26
00:01:29,583 --> 00:01:33,083
all your resignation letters
in that time.

27
00:01:36,166 --> 00:01:38,083
When's Phil coming in?

28
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:42,875
He turned us down.

29
00:01:43,833 --> 00:01:46,583
I've got a few
stronger candidates.

30
00:01:48,875 --> 00:01:51,458
I told you
he was our best shot.

31
00:01:51,458 --> 00:01:53,041
He's stubborn.

32
00:01:53,041 --> 00:01:54,375
If he's not interested,

33
00:01:54,375 --> 00:01:55,833
you can't change his mind.

34
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:58,583
Or did you just
not try hard enough?

35
00:02:01,291 --> 00:02:03,458
He's not interested
in dating shows.

36
00:02:04,625 --> 00:02:06,250
Who says I'm not?

37
00:02:11,833 --> 00:02:13,500
How'd you get in here?

38
00:02:14,125 --> 00:02:15,791
Through the door.

39
00:02:15,791 --> 00:02:16,750
Now that you're here,

40
00:02:16,750 --> 00:02:18,041
let's talk.

41
00:02:18,041 --> 00:02:20,000
I'm interested
in your dating show.

42
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:25,250
But I have one condition.

43
00:02:26,791 --> 00:02:28,291
Let's hear it.

44
00:02:28,291 --> 00:02:29,625
Everything's negotiable.

45
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:35,000
I want Cole

46
00:02:37,041 --> 00:02:38,791
as my producer.

47
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,583
Easy enough.

48
00:02:42,583 --> 00:02:45,250
Every cast member
gets a producer.

49
00:02:45,541 --> 00:02:47,000
And Cole's yours.

50
00:03:02,625 --> 00:03:04,791
Let's start with
a quick interview.

51
00:03:05,291 --> 00:03:07,375
Just so we can
get to know each other.

52
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:09,333
Sure.

53
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:12,416
Have you ever been
in a relationship?

54
00:03:14,791 --> 00:03:16,500
Not really.

55
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:18,583
But I almost had one once.

56
00:03:19,958 --> 00:03:21,125
He knows.

57
00:03:21,791 --> 00:03:25,625
Wow! What happened
between you two in high school?

58
00:03:25,625 --> 00:03:29,041
Let's switch gears.
What's your type?

59
00:03:29,041 --> 00:03:30,291
Wait.

60
00:03:30,291 --> 00:03:32,250
Let Phil finish.

61
00:03:34,291 --> 00:03:36,250
I just follow my heart.

62
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:38,166
When I fall for someone,

63
00:03:38,166 --> 00:03:39,875
I don't give up easily.

64
00:03:40,666 --> 00:03:41,583
Unless...

65
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:45,000
their heart belongs
to someone else.

66
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,291
You've dated a lot,
haven't you?

67
00:03:54,291 --> 00:03:55,750
I'm not the one
on the show.

68
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:58,791
Why would I tell you
about my love life?

69
00:03:58,791 --> 00:04:00,041
You're the scriptwriter.

70
00:04:00,041 --> 00:04:01,916
You're writing
my storyline.

71
00:04:01,916 --> 00:04:04,125
I need to know
how you see love.

72
00:04:04,125 --> 00:04:05,791
Makes it easier
to work with you.

73
00:04:08,583 --> 00:04:09,916
You don't.

74
00:04:11,375 --> 00:04:14,125
Let's do a quick
personality quiz.

75
00:04:14,125 --> 00:04:15,625
Get a feel for you.

76
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:26,750
Hey, guys! I'm Jan.

77
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:28,875
Check out this outfit.

78
00:04:28,875 --> 00:04:30,916
I've got a secret mission.

79
00:04:30,916 --> 00:04:33,875
I'll be working undercover
as a server

80
00:04:33,875 --> 00:04:35,375
at The Coach.

81
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:36,083
In a minute,

82
00:04:36,083 --> 00:04:38,791
I'll mask up
and serve tables.

83
00:04:38,791 --> 00:04:40,291
Hopefully
I can pull it off

84
00:04:40,291 --> 00:04:42,416
without anyone
recognizing me.

85
00:04:53,291 --> 00:04:56,041
Here's your
ricotta toast, sir.

86
00:04:56,041 --> 00:04:57,416
And your hot chocolate.

87
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:03,875
For your hot chocolate,

88
00:05:03,875 --> 00:05:06,000
I'd recommend adding this.

89
00:05:07,291 --> 00:05:08,791
Sorry! Sorry!

90
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:11,416
I'm so sorry.

91
00:05:12,166 --> 00:05:13,791
What's your name?

92
00:05:14,875 --> 00:05:15,666
Oops.

93
00:05:16,541 --> 00:05:18,583
Busted.

94
00:05:22,125 --> 00:05:24,125
I was asking your name.

95
00:05:24,125 --> 00:05:25,750
I didn't ask
to see your face.

96
00:05:27,125 --> 00:05:30,875
I'm Jan. January.

97
00:05:32,375 --> 00:05:33,250
Excuse me.

98
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:40,125
Your employee damaged
my MIDI keyboard.

99
00:05:40,125 --> 00:05:41,583
Somebody's
gonna pay for it.

100
00:05:41,583 --> 00:05:43,291
I don't care
if it's the café

101
00:05:43,291 --> 00:05:44,875
or your employee...

102
00:05:47,166 --> 00:05:48,583
February.

103
00:05:49,833 --> 00:05:51,625
March? April?

104
00:05:52,875 --> 00:05:53,666
May.

105
00:05:56,625 --> 00:05:57,833
Stop filming.

106
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:01,791
I'm so sorry.

107
00:06:23,166 --> 00:06:24,000
Henry.

108
00:06:24,708 --> 00:06:26,083
Still working?

109
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:29,541
Lisa wants me to find
a new angle on the cast.

110
00:06:41,875 --> 00:06:43,333
You're worried

111
00:06:43,625 --> 00:06:45,416
about your probation, huh?

112
00:06:48,375 --> 00:06:50,583
You'll be fine.

113
00:06:50,583 --> 00:06:53,041
Lisa can be

114
00:06:53,041 --> 00:06:55,041
pretty demanding.

115
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:57,250
But

116
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:59,250
she'll give you a shot.

117
00:07:09,208 --> 00:07:10,666
Phil comes off

118
00:07:11,375 --> 00:07:12,916
like a jerk.

119
00:07:13,791 --> 00:07:14,791
But

120
00:07:16,958 --> 00:07:18,708
he's actually

121
00:07:20,708 --> 00:07:22,583
very thoughtful.

122
00:07:25,708 --> 00:07:27,666
He's always there.

123
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:34,125
Once you get to know him,

124
00:07:36,625 --> 00:07:38,041
you'll realize

125
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,750
he's got a soft side.

126
00:07:46,416 --> 00:07:48,041
He can be vulnerable.

127
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,958
It makes you
want to look out for him.

128
00:08:00,625 --> 00:08:02,750
You really know him.

129
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:04,333
Let me grab you a coffee.

130
00:08:04,333 --> 00:08:05,833
We can keep talking.

131
00:08:05,833 --> 00:08:07,083
I'm good.

132
00:08:07,083 --> 00:08:08,625
Coffee keeps me up.

133
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,083
I'd better get going.

134
00:08:31,541 --> 00:08:32,375
Yaowei!

135
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:37,875
Jing Tong,
have you seen Phil?

136
00:08:41,375 --> 00:08:42,166
Nope.

137
00:08:42,708 --> 00:08:45,958
Let's split up
and meet by the stairs.

138
00:08:45,958 --> 00:08:46,750
Okay?

139
00:08:47,416 --> 00:08:48,250
Wait.

140
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:54,500
There's something
I need to tell you.

141
00:08:54,791 --> 00:08:57,791
The party's about to start.
Can it wait?

142
00:08:58,791 --> 00:08:59,875
Chen Yaowei!

143
00:09:03,166 --> 00:09:05,083
That's exactly why.

144
00:09:06,166 --> 00:09:08,500
Can you just hear me out?

145
00:09:51,041 --> 00:09:53,083
Please don't reject me.

146
00:10:00,458 --> 00:10:02,583
You can fool
everyone else.

147
00:10:05,583 --> 00:10:07,083
But not me.

148
00:10:10,166 --> 00:10:11,333
You only have eyes

149
00:10:13,208 --> 00:10:15,125
for Phil.

150
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:27,708
You're wrong.

